Package org.chronos.chronodb.internal.api

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    BranchInternal
    An extended version of the Branch interface.
    BranchManagerInternal
    An extended version of the BranchManager interface.
    ChronoDBConfiguration
    This class represents the configuration of a single ChronoDB instance.
    ChronoDBFactoryInternal
    Extended version of the ChronoDBFactory interface.
    ChronoDBInternal
    An interface that defines methods on ChronoDB for internal use.
    ChronoDBInternal.ChronoNonReturningJob
    A functional interface that represents a job to be executed on a ChronoDB or one of its components.
    ChronoDBInternal.ChronoReturningJob<T>
    A functional interface that represents a job to be executed on a ChronoDB or one of its components.
    CommitMetadataStore
    A CommitMetadataStore is a store in the ChronosBackend that contains metadata objects for commit operations.
    GetResult<T>
    A GetResult is returned by a TemporalDataMatrix.get(long, String).
    Lockable
    A Lockable is any object that can be locked exclusively or non-exclusively using the try-with-resources pattern.
    Lockable.LockHolder
    A Lockable.LockHolder is an object that represents ownership over some sort of Lock.
    MutableTransactionConfiguration
    The mutable portion of a ChronoDBTransaction.Configuration.
    Period
    A Period is a range (or interval) of timestamps.
    TemporalDataMatrix
    A TemporalDataMatrix is a structured container for temporal key-value pairs.
    TemporalKeyValueStore
    A TemporalKeyValueStore (or TKVS) is a collection of named keyspaces, which in turn contain temporal key-value pairs.
    TransactionConfigurationInternal
    An extended version of ChronoDBTransaction.Configuration.
